on":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rip apart, to rend the seam, to cleave, to break apart, to crack"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to split open, to cut open, to slit open, to crack"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lance, to lacerate, to gash, to cut, to make an incision"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to breakfast, to have breakfast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَطَرَ (faṭara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"crack, fissure, rift, rupture, cleavage"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"breaking of the fast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fungi, mushrooms","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shape, to make, to form, to create, to fashion, to compose, to bring forth","examples":[{"text":"فَسَيَقُولُونَ مَنْ يُعِيدُنَا قُلِ الَّذِي فَطَرَكُمْ أَوَّلَ مَرَّةٍ","english":"Then they will say, “Who will bring us back?” Say, “The One Who created you the first time.”"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to endow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَطَرَ (faṭara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of فِطْرَة (fiṭra, “nature, disposition, constitution, temperament, instinct”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate to Hebrew פָטַר (pāṭar, “to set free, to let out, to release, to dismiss”), Aramaic פָטַר (pāṭar, “to cleave, to separate, to free, to discharge”), Aramaic פְטַר (pəṭar, “to free, to release, to dismiss”), Classical Syriac ܦܛܰܪ (pṭar, “to leave, to desist from; to shoot out; to separate, to dissolve; to dismiss”), Ugaritic 𐎔𐎉𐎗 (pṭr, “to split”), hypercorrected Ugaritic 𐎔𐎑𐎗 (pẓr, “to free, to loosen, to let go”), Akkadian 𒃮 (DUḪ /⁠paṭāru⁠/, “to loosen, to detach; to relax, to slacken; to release, to let free; to disperse”), and Ge'ez ፈጠረ (fäṭärä, “to carve; to feign; to create”) which has been borrowed into a second فَطَرَ (faṭara).\n\nFrom Ge'ez ፈጠረ (fäṭärä). Doublet of the former فَطَرَ (faṭara) for the Ethiopic one is cognate."},"ipa":null}